</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>The mathematical difficulty of processing a block automatically adjusts so it always takes about 10 minutes. Blockchain length should not be a problem, as I understand it. The problem is that the older versions of the software can only process so many transactions in a block, so if there are too many transactions within a 10 minute period, there will be delays. How they sort this out with rolling back to older software then switching to newer versions, I'll wait and see.</p>

  </div>
